<p>The Norwegian Nobel Institute said Venezuelan opposition leader María Corina Machado cannot give, share, or transfer her Nobel Peace Prize to anyone else, after she suggested she would like to give or share her 2025 award with U.S. President Donald Trump. The institute said Nobel Prize decisions are final and permanent under the Nobel Foundation’s statutes, and prizes cannot be appealed, revoked, or reassigned.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/8etpfnEtztOnM8vsalQkLS2fvdHMDznQ0srnFpw6eQJP4D6HsyzBGEPw30aOuIBkBP0fnOWLQlC5Rlhu5gN8FgwqJ7FJLgjKZ7ccixW1uHPGPUOdDxOXS8xWSxp__Bv8YYw3-FvHTy1-fxApOUdV8UE0ZO3OjKORhwSwcoBXq8UcxARgGOA' alt='María Corina Machado, Venezuela’s opposition leader, offered to give her Nobel Peace Prize to President Trump, who has long coveted the award.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Rules cited: The institute pointed to the Nobel Foundation’s statutes in explaining that the Peace Prize cannot be transferred, shared, or revoked once awarded.</li><li>Trump interest: The New York Times reported that President Trump has long coveted the Nobel Peace Prize, which helped draw extra attention to Machado’s remarks.</li><li>Media spotlight: The episode quickly spread beyond traditional outlets, with the discussion circulating widely on social media threads such as Reddit’s r/inthenews.</li></ul><blockquote>The decision is final and stands for all time, - Norwegian Nobel Institute (statement)</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Norwegian Nobel Institute: It says Nobel Peace Prizes cannot be transferred to others and that the award decision is final under the Nobel Foundation’s rules. (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/nobel-institute-says-venezuelan-leader-machado-cant-give-peace-prize-to-trump/article70496857.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li><li>María Corina Machado: She indicated she would like to give or share her Nobel Peace Prize with President Trump. (<a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/maria-corina-machado-cant-give-nobel-peace-prize-to-trump-organization-says/'>CBS News</a>)</li><li>South China Morning Post (reporting emphasis): It highlighted that the statutes do not allow appeals and that Nobel committees do not comment further on decisions. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/europe/article/3339469/nobel-panel-rejects-machados-idea-give-her-peace-prize-trump'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/nobel-institute-says-venezuelan-leader-machado-cant-give-peace-prize-to-trump/article70496857.ece'>Nobel Institute says Venezuelan leader Machado can&#x27;t give Peace Prize to Trump</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/europe/article/3339469/nobel-panel-rejects-machados-idea-give-her-peace-prize-trump'>Nobel panel rejects Machado’s idea to give her Peace Prize to Trump</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/maria-corina-machado-cant-give-nobel-peace-prize-to-trump-organization-says/'>Machado can&#x27;t give Nobel Peace Prize to Trump, organization says</a> - cbsnews.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2026/01/10/world/americas/trump-nobel-peace-prize-maria-machado.html'>Machado Offered Trump Her Nobel, but Prize Institute Says It’s Not Allowed</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.reddit.com/r/inthenews/comments/1q9macu/nobel_institute_says_machados_peace_prize_cannot/'>Nobel Institute says Machado&#x27;s Peace Prize cannot be &#x27;transferred&#x27; to Trump</a> - reddit.com</li></ul>